changes.detail: Added new route path '/projects/:projectId/inspections/:inspectionId/checklist' with MobileChecklistPage component

patterns_discovered.description: Route follows established nested project structure pattern: /projects/:projectId/inspections/:inspectionId/checklist
Consistent import pattern used for page components from ./pages/ directory
Route placed after project detail routes but before global routes (/approvals, /audit), following architectural hierarchy

gotchas_discovered.description: New route appears to be placed at the parent Route level rather than nested within the /projects/:projectId route group, which may create routing inconsistencies
Route imports MobileChecklistPage component but component file must exist at frontend/src/pages/MobileChecklistPage.tsx - missing in this diff

approach_outcome.description: Route successfully added to App.tsx with proper import statement and route definition
approach_outcome.notes: Route definition is complete but implementation depends on MobileChecklistPage component being present in the codebase

recommendations.recommendation: Verify MobileChecklistPage.tsx exists in frontend/src/pages/ directory to prevent runtime import errors
Consider nesting the checklist route within the /projects/:projectId route group for better route hierarchy and consistency
Add end-to-end tests to verify the route correctly loads MobileChecklistPage and passes projectId and inspectionId parameters
Document the route structure and parameter passing mechanism for future route additions
